#title
Partner × Bankrate API Spec

::

::page-section

## Overview

This document describes the integration between Partner and Bankrate. Partner authenticates via Bankrate Gateway API keys. Two server-side endpoints are exposed by Bankrate to support user profile sync and client token generation.

---

## Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Partner
    participant Bankrate

    Partner->>Bankrate: POST /profile/v1/update-user-profile<br/>(Bankrate Gateway API key + PII)
    Bankrate-->>Partner: 200 OK { bankrate_user_id }

    Partner->>Bankrate: POST /profile/v1/generate-user-client-token<br/>(Bankrate Gateway API key + partner_user_id)
    Bankrate-->>Partner: 200 OK { bankrate-user-client-token: JWT }
```

---

## Authentication

All endpoints require a Bankrate Gateway API key passed in the request header.

| Header        | Value                        |
|---------------|------------------------------|
| `x-api-key`   | `<bankrate-gateway-api-key>` |

API keys are created and managed by Partner in the Bankrate Gateway.

---

## Endpoints

### `POST /profile/v1/update-user-profile`

  Called **server-side by Partner at time of user login**. Creates or updates a Bankrate User Profile using PII data from Partner.

